{"lemma":"صَلِف","slug":"صَلِف","root":"ص.ل.ف","root_slug":"ص-ل-ف","root_link":"/words/roots/ص-ل-ف","pos":"ADJ","pos_camel":"adj","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["adj","noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n24781"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B5%D9%8E%D9%84%D9%90%D9%81"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of صَلِفَ (ṣalifa) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"conceit, arrogance"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"boastful, blustering"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Verbal noun of صَلِفَ (ṣalifa)."},"ipa":["/sˤa.laf/","/sˤa.lif/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n24781","headword_ar":"صَلِفٌ","root":"Slf","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", applied to clouds ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saHaAb","text_ar":"سَحَاب"},{"kind":"text","text":", S, M, O, K),"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Containing no water:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having little water and much thunder."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K. [Said in the TA to be tropical; but I doubt its being so.]) It is said in a prov.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rub~a SalifK taHota Alr~aAEidapi","text_ar":"رُبَّ صَلِفٍ تَحْتَ الرَّاعِدَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, and so in some copies of the K,) or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rub~a SalafK","text_ar":"رُبَّ صَلَفٍ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, O, and so in some copies of the K, [with an inf. n. in the place of an epithet,]) i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Many a cloud is there,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"many clouds are there, lacking rain,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having much thunder with little rain,"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"beneath that which thunders:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] (A'Obeyd, O:) applied to the wealthy niggard: (A'Obeyd, O, K:) or to him who threatens, and does not perform what he threatens: (S, O, K:) or to him who commends himself much, (M, O, K,) and is loquacious, (M, O,) but is destitute of good. (M, O, K.) ―         -b2-  And A vessel"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that takes little water:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, S, M, O, K:) a"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"small"},{"kind":"text","text":"vessel: one"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that leaks; that will not hold water."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, TA. [This, also, is said in the TA to be tropical.]) And A"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"heavy"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and thick"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA) vessel. (K, TA.) ―         -b3-  Also High ground ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"quf~","text_ar":"قُفّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"), or a hard plain,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that produces no plants"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"herbage:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) and so the fem., with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":", applied to land ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aroD","text_ar":"اَرْض"},{"kind":"text","text":"). (M, TA.) ―         -b4-  Wheat ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaEaAm","text_ar":"طَعَام"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having little increase"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaliylu Aln~azali","text_ar":"قَلِيلُ النَّزَلِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alr~ayoEi","text_ar":"الرَّيْعِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"): (M:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tasteless:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, O, K:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaliyfN","text_ar":"صَلِيفٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the same, in the former sense or in the latter. (M.) ―         -b5-  And [A man]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"heavy in soul,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"spirit;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vaqiylu Alr~uwHi","text_ar":"ثَقِيلُ الرُّوحِ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA. [See 4, second sentence, which shows that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muSolifN","text_ar":"مُصْلِفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"has this meaning: but the epithet thus expl. in the TA is there said to be like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"katifN","text_ar":"كَتِفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]) ―         -b6-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SalifapN","text_ar":"صَلِفَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies A woman"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"not in favour with,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"not beloved by,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, O, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"her husband,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"him by whom she is supported;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M;) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hated by him:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SalaAy^ifu","text_ar":"صَلَايِفُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, O, K,) which is extr. [in respect of analogy], (M,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SalifaAtN","text_ar":"صَلِفَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (O, K.) ―         -b7-  See also 1, near the end."}],"source_refs":["M","S","O","K","IAar","TA"]}]}}